A 29-year-old man, Taofeek Oseni, on Tuesday, appeared before a Chief Magistrates’ Court in Osogbo for allegedly stealing some motor parts worth N78,000. The police charged Oseni with two counts of conspiracy and theft. The Prosecutor, ASP John Idoko, told the court that the defendant committed the offences on Sept. 14 at Dada Estate, Osogbo. ALSO READ: Buhari redeploys Keyamo, Alasoadura in minor cabinet reshuffle Idoko said that the defendant stole three car radiators, one Peugeot 407 shock absorber and some other used parts, the property of Mr Bashiru Sambo. He said that the offences contravened Sections 383(1), 309(9) and 414 of the Criminal Law of Osun, 2002. 2020 UTME: JAMB urges candidates to get NIN Buhari congratulates Anglican Primate-elect, Archbishop… JUST IN: Unknown gunmen kill butchers association chairman… Police burst armed robbers, kidnappers’ den in Bauchi The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Defence Counsel, Mr B. Y. Dada prayed the court to grant his client bail in the most liberal terms. The Magistrate, Mrs M. A. Awodele, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50,000, with two sureties in like sum. He said that the two sureties should reside within the court’s jurisdiction and swear to an affidavit of means. The magistrate thereafter adjourned the case until Oct. 15 for mention. NAN Here is how i overcome QUICK RELEASE and make it BIGGER, STRONGER And LONGER with this NAFDAC APPROVED NATURAL REMEDY. Click now!! FINALLY REVEALED! ''After Many Months Of Research,Woman Finally Discovered What Top Men Use TO Last During 'S*X' Like a 23 Year Old in Bed Click Here To Read More!!!